article.headline: Columbia 59, Dartmouth 50
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- John Baumann scored 25 points, making all 13 of his free throw attempts, to lead Columbia to a 59-50 victory over Dartmouth on Friday night. The Lions (11-11, 4-3 Ivy League) broke a 45-all tie on a fadeaway in the paint by Niko Scott with 5:13 remaining and never trailed again. Alex Barnett had a 14 points and 10 rebounds to lead Dartmouth (8-13, 1-6). DeVon Mosley added 13 points. The Lions hit only 1-of-11 3-point shots but made 20-of-22 free throws. Bauman, who also grabbed nine rebounds and shot 6-of-9 from the field, scored 15 points in the first half, including seven straight at the end of a 13-0 run that gave Columbia a 24-14 lead. Dartmouth drew within 26-24 at the break. Dartmouth took its first lead of the second half on a turn around jump shot by Barnett that made it 37-36 with 12:29 remaining. A Barnett jumper with 5:43 left tied the game for the seventh and last time before the Lions finished with a 14-5 run that included 6-for-6 from the foul line.
